      "id": 1,
      "text": "Naples town was founded in 1789 as part of the Phelps and Gorham Purchase.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        23,
        24
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naples%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In 1808, the settlement adopted the name Naples, replacing earlier names like Watkinstown and Middletown.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        26
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naples%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Grapes first planted in the 1860s ignited a wine industry that now celebrates an annual Grape Festival, first held in 1961.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        29
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naples%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Landmark Society finished a historic resources survey of Naples in 2019, cataloging the village’s architectural heritage.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
